article.headline: Florida 74, Winthrop 45
article.story: EDS: APNewsNow. Florida 74, Winthrop 45. By STEVEN WINE AP Sports Writer SUNRISE, Fla. -- Chandler Parsons led an early surge to help the Florida Gators score the first 22 points, and they beat Winthrop 74-45 Sunday in the Orange Bowl Classic. After the quick start, Florida had scoring runs of 10 points to lead 36-4 and nine to go up 50-7. It was 53-11 at halftime. Parsons, who needed only 19 minutes to total 17 points, had nine before Winthrop scored. The Gators (10-2) will begin the new year with at least 10 wins for the fourth season in a row. They extended their winning streak in the Orange Bowl Classic to nine games, and they've won their past 14 neutral-site games in Florida. Florida State won the opener in the one-day event, beating Western Kentucky 82-69. Winthrop (1-10) endured its 10th consecutive defeat. The Eagles lost four of top six players from team that made the NCAA tournament last season.
